{
  "texts": [
    "Table definitionThis paper mainly focuses on (semi-)structured tables, which are grids of cells arranged in rows and columns [26].",
    "Every column in a table signifies a specific attribute, each having its own data type (e.g., numeric, string, or date).",
    "Each row forms a record populated with diverse attribute values.",
    "A cell is the intersection of a row and a column.",
    "Cells are basic units to store text, numerical values, formulas, etc."
  ]
}